# UNPACK address whose optimized binary entrypoint suffix is a single
# non-UTF-8 byte (0xff): the issue's `ep_nonascii` case. L1 stores the
# entrypoint name as a raw byte string (Entrypoint.value_encoding /
# Non_empty_string: length <= 31, not "default") with no UTF-8 check and
# accepts this; MIR used to represent the entrypoint as a UTF-8 string and
# rejected it (L2-1377). The Michelson interface now matches L1 and pushes
# Some. The decoded address has a non-UTF-8 entrypoint, which is not
# expressible as a Michelson string literal, so the result is mapped to a
# bool via IF_NONE (the same differential method used to find the divergence).
code { UNPACK address ; IF_NONE { PUSH bool False } { DROP ; PUSH bool True } } ;
input { Stack_elt bytes 0x050a0000001700007b09f782e0bcd67739510afa819d85976119d5efff } ;
output { Stack_elt bool True }
